wine spoken of in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/2.1-11"},"John 2:1–11"],"was a drink made from the “‘fruit of the vine’ (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/26.29"},"Matt. 26:29"],"), a light, sweet wine (normally unfermented); eaten with bread it was one of the staple foods of the day” (",["span.emphasis","Doctrinal New Testament Commentary,"],"1:136)."],[".figure",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-2-jesus-begins-his-work.f9"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","What effect did this miracle have on Jesus’ followers? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/2.11"},"v. 11"],")."]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What did they (and you) learn about Jesus from what He did in this story?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Cleansing the Temple"],[".",{"id":"f10","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-2-jesus-begins-his-work.f10"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-077-1.gif"}]],[".figure",{"id":"f11","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-2-jesus-begins-his-work.f11"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","According to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/2.13-17"},"John 2:13–17"],", what did Jesus do that upset so many people? Why?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What does this account teach us about how Jesus wants us to treat God’s sacred buildings?"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","List three things you could do to show more reverence for a house of God."]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-c.gif"}],"A Temple Raised in Three Days?"],["p.para",{"id":"p72","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-2-jesus-begins-his-work.p72"},"What “temple” was Jesus referring to in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/2.19"},"John 2:19"],"(see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/27.62-64"},"Matthew 27:62–64"],"for additional help)."]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
